Five-Year Accident History

Within the past five years, the Putnam Plant has not had any accidental releases that resulted in injuries or property damage.

Emergency Response

In the event that a chlorine release does occur, the Putnam Plant has an emergency response program that coordinates emergency response with the regional emergency management agency and the Local Emergency Planning Committee. If such a release did occur, plant personnel would contact the local emergency responders who would dispatch a trained HAZMAT team to the site to handle the chlorine release. 

